article.headline: Vermont 64, New Hampshire 54
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. (AP) -- T.J. Sorrentine scored 16 points and Taylor Coppenrath 14 to lead Vermont to a 64-54 victory Wednesday night over New Hampshire. Vermont (12-3 overall and 7-0 in America east) appeared to be running away with the game midway in the first half with a 13-point lead at 25-12 following a pair of Coppenrath freethrows. But UNH closed to within seven points to 33-26 in favor of Vermont at the half. New Hampshire ( 6-10 overall, 2-5 in the league), closed to within three points at 37-34 with 15:30 to play in the game but Vermont responded again to open the lead to 15 points at 57-52. UNH could get no closer than eight points at 60-52 with 1:16 to play. New Hampshire was led in scoring by Ben Sturgill and Jermaine Anderson with 16 points each. Josh Duell contributed 13 points for Vermont.
